The battery, whose role is to store energy and release it when the sunlight is insufficient; the mathematical lead acid battery model used is given by [24, 25]. It is modelled by putting in series an electromotive force corresponding to the open circuit voltage when it is charged Eb, a capacity indicating the internal capacity of a battery (Cb) and an internal resistance Rb, Fig. 4 gives the equivalent circuit. The terminal voltage of the battery is given by:Fig. 4
